  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN169-kilavi">talaimaka ṉiṭaccurattut taṉṉeñciṟkuc colliyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">What HE said to his heart in the middle of the desert.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="AN169">
        <l><anchor n="1"/>marantalai karintu nilampayam vāṭa</l>
        <l>valaṅkukatir vēynta vaḻaṟikaḻ naṉantalaip</l>
        <l>pulitolait tuṇṭa peruṅkaḷiṟ ṟoḻiyūṉ</l>
        <l>kalikeḻu maṟavar kāḻkkōt toḻinta</l>
        <l>ñe<supplied>li</supplied>kōṟ ciṟutī māṭṭi yolitiraik</l>
        <l>kaṭalviḷai yamiḻtiṉ kaṇañcā lumaṇar</l>
        <l>cuṉaiko <supplied>ṭīnī</supplied>rc cōṟṟulaik kūṭṭuñ</l>
        <l>curampala kaṭantu namvayiṟ paṭarntu<supplied>na</supplied>ṉi</l>
        <l>pacalai pāynta mēṉiya <supplied>ṇe</supplied>ṭituniṉaintu</l>
        <l>celkatir maḻuṅkiya pulampukoṇ mālai</l>
        <l>melviral cēttiya nutaliṉ malkik</l>
        <l>kayalumiḻ nīriṟ kaṇpaṉi vārap</l>
        <l>peruntō ṇekiḻtta cellalō</l>
        <l>varuntumā laḷiya ṭiruntiḻai tāṉē.</l> 
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>[In her heart] setting out for us, crossing many deserts, (8)</l>
        <l>where, in the vast area glittering with fire that covers the swaying ears, (2)</l>
        <l>so that the tops of the trees are charred [and] the yield of the land fades, (1)</l>
        <l>the salt merchants, many in a group, kindle a little fire with the bamboo sticks</l>
        <l>that stayed behind after boisterous bold men had strung on spits</l>
        <l>the meat left over from a large elephant bull that a tiger had killed [and] eaten</l>
        <l>[and] join the ambrosia ripened in the sea with sounding waves</l>
        <l>in the pot of cooked rice with sweet water taken from a mountain pool, (3-7)</l>
        <l>she with a body that is much spread over by pallor, thinking for a long [moment] (9)</l>
        <l>in lonely evenings when the departing [sun] rays are blunted, (10)</l>
        <l>while, abounding on [her] forehead on which soft fingers dwell, (11)</l>
        <l>tears flow over from [her] eyes, like water that is spouted by [two] carps, (12)</l>
        <l>– ah, the unhappiness that emaciated [her] wide shoulders – (13)</l>
        <l>she is suffering indeed, pitiable her, she with perfect jewels. (14)</l>
      </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
  </text>

